Belarusian Potash Corp., a trading
arm of Russian producer OAO  Uralkali (URKA) , will supply 400,000 metric
tons of potash to  India  at $490 a ton from September to March,
after the sale of 1.2 million tons last week at the same price.  BPC agreed to sell the potash to Zuari Industries Ltd.,
Indiaâ€™s second-largest importer of the soil nutrient, market
research FMB said in a note.  Alexey Sotskov, a spokesman for Uralkali in Moscow,
confirmed the details, while declining to elaborate.  To contact the reporter on this story:
